ibituo Technology LBT-T300-HW1 Web Management start_single_service buffer overflow', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 03 May 2026 02:17:12 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-7674', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['A flaw has been found in Shenzhen Libituo Technology LBT-T300-HW1 up to 1.2.8. This issue affects the function start_single_service of the component Web Management Interface. Executing a manipulation of the argument vpn_pptp_server/vpn_l2tp_server can lead to buffer overflow. The attack can be executed remotely. The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-7674vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-7674weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['cna@vuldb.com', 'hey@cvefeed.io'], 'url': ['https://github.com/hmKunlun/lbt-t300-hw1/blob/main/reselov_vpn_server%EF%BC%88vpn_pptp_server%EF%BC%89.md', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/800705', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/800706', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/360827', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/360827/cti'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-7674']}}, {'title': 'Instructure discloses second data breach in less than a year', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 00:00:46 +0000', 'source': 'https://databreaches.net/2026/05/03/instructure-discloses-second-data-breach-in-less-than-a-year/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=instructure-discloses-second-data-breach-in-less-than-a-year', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['databreaches.net']}}, {'title': 'Marcus & Millichap - 1,837,078 breached accounts - https://www.redpacketsecurity.com/marcus-millichap-1-837-078-breached-accounts/#databreach #HaveIBeenPwnedLatestBreaches #HIBP #OSINT #Security #threatintel #TroyHunt', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 02:11:56 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@RedPacketSecurity/116513835001471426', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['redpacketsecurity.com'], 'email-addr': ['RedPacketSecurity@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Marcus & Millichap - 1,837,078 breached accounts', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 01:15:42 +0000', 'source': 'https://haveibeenpwned.com/Breach/MarcusMillichap', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['In April 2026, the commercial real estate brokerage firmMarcus & Millichap was named as one of multiple alleged victims of the ShinyHunters hacking and extortion group. Data alleged to have been obtained from the company was subsequently released publicly and included 1.8M unique email addresses, along with names, phone numbers and employment-related information including employer, job title and physical company address. Intheir disclosure notice, Marcus & Millichap advised that data which may have been accessed appeared limited to "company forms, templates, marketing materials, and general contact information".'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': "Can't say much about this due to an injunction (which I am sure the threat actor will ignore), but I can say this is yet *another* new ransomware operation.#ransomware #databreach #cybersecurity https://www.cyberdaily.au/security/13537-exclusive-kiwi-electrical-contractor-confirms-cyber-attack", 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 01:11:24 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@David_Hollingworth/116513545638111780', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cyberdaily.au'], 'email-addr': ['David_Hollingworth@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Trellix suffers a breach exposing part of its source code. The company is working with experts and law enforcement to address the issue. Details are limited. #Cybersecurity #DataBreach https://thehackernews.com/2026/05/trellix-confirms-source-code-breach.html', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 04 May 2026 00:09:35 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@technoholic/116513241794993797', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['technoholic.me', 'thehackernews.com'], 'email-addr': ['technoholic@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Instructure Breach Exposes Data of 275 Million UsersA recent data breach at Instructure, the company behind Canvas, has compromised the sensitive information of 275 million users, including names, email addresses, student ID numbers, and private messages. The company is actively investigating the incident with cybersecurity experts and law enforcement.https://osintsights.com/instructure-breach-exposes-data-of-275-million-users?utm_source=mastodon&utm_medium=social#EducationTechnology #DataBreach #Instructure #Canvas #EmergingThreats', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 03 May 2026 23:08:24 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@Analyst207/116513065372892506', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['osintsights.com'], 'email-addr': ['Analyst207@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': "See's Candies, Vimeo, Liberty Mutual Insurance, Carnival Cruises, Pitney Bowes, ADT and more are all part of this week's mess!#News #TechNews #Cybersecurity #DataBreach #Ransomwarehttps://youtu.be/q4Q2F0IDTnA", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 03 May 2026 20:05:32 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@NickAEsp/116512265701760520', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['NickAEsp@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': "Daily podcast: See's Candies, Vimeo, Liberty Mutual Insurance, Carnival Cruises, Pitney Bowes, ADT and more are all part of this week's mess!#News #TechNews #Cybersecurity #DataBreach #Ransomware #podcasthttps://soundcloud.com/nickaesp/b2026-05-03", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 03 May 2026 20:05:32 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@NickAEsp/116512265495072655', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['soundcloud.com'], 'email-addr': ['NickAEsp@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Marcus & Millichap - 1,837,078 breached accounts', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 03 May 2026 22:53:12 Z', 'source': 'https://haveibeenpwned.com/Breach/MarcusMillichap', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['In April 2026, the commercial real estate brokerage firmMarcus & Millichap was named as one of multiple alleged victims of the ShinyHunters hacking and extortion group. Data alleged to have been obtained from the company was subsequently released publicly and included 1.8M unique email addresses, along with names, phone numbers and employment-related information including employer, job title and physical company address. Intheir disclosure notice, Marcus & Millichap advised that data which may have been accessed appeared limited to "company forms, templates, marketing materials, and general contact information".'], 'observables': {}}]